CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 11, 1961, pg. 25, reads: "Happy Birthday - Robin Bullard, aided by many of her little friends, celebrated her birthday last Saturday with a delightful party given at 2801 Bedford Ave., the home of her parents, Robin (shown cutting the cake) was escorted by 'Champ' Andrews. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Robin Bullard wearing striped hat, posed behind round cake with three candles inscribed "Happy Birthday Robin, surrounded by other girls, and boys, possibly including "Champ" Andrews wearing plaid jacket, in Bullard home, 2801 Bedford Avenue
